author: Olayinka
message: In this dispensation where knowledge is available for all. Nothing should stop you from learning.  Have you been wishing to take courses online and get certifications but you can't afford the amount for the course.  Do you know that Coursera offers you opportunity to learn for free through its financial aid platform? Oh, you must have heard about it.  Probably you don't know how to go about it or someone close to you needs to apply for some courses. (Trust me, Coursera has great courses).   Well, I have written a comprehensive article that simplifies this application process. Just 5 minutes read!   With this you can learn any course on Coursera and get certification.  More importantly, learn to apply! Let's keep learning and developing ourselves!  After reading this article, make sure you clap if you'd like it.   Check out the article here: https://link.medium.com/9vhlxIyH02  Regards, Olayinka Arimoro

message: Know any women considering a career in cybersecurity? Encourage them check out the Women in CyberSecurity (WiCyS) Security Training Scholarship made possible by Google, Bloomberg LP, and Facebook.  The focus of this scholarship is to award WiCyS members who are seeking cybersecurity employment within the next 1.5 years. The program is designed for students and/or career changers!  The multi-stage program includes the SANS Institute‚Äôs world class training and certifications.  Applications are due 2 August 2021. As the scholarship is for WiCyS members, this is an excellent time for aspiring cybersecurity professionals to join the organization.  We need more women in cybersecurity.   Please help spread the word!  Register as a member and apply for the scholarship using this link:  https://www.wicys.org/benefits/security-training-scholarship/

message: Read both books like a buffet üòÇüòÇ else you get bored of it.  Start with the Kimball one I just start am yesterday.  Kimball is called the Father of Data Warehouse because he started the whole Dimension modelling idea stuff.   Use this guide from this blog on how to read the book  https://www.holistics.io/blog/how-to-read-data-warehouse-toolkit/  Though some of the ideas there from my research won't apply again as a result of the advent of MPP & ELT approach to DW but the fundamental knowledge of Dimensional modelling still valid.  So you may need to scheme through some sections

message: Are you a skilled data scientist looking for internship? Apply here:  https://bit.ly/datainternshipng

Hello guys  I got an invite to partake in Omdena challenge some weeks back. In the course of the project, I was given a code due to my performance.  The essence of this code is, you stand a better chance of getting an invite to take part in Omdena challenge whenever you apply. All you do is to fill the application form of any project you want to partake. While filling the form, you will see a field "where did you hear about us", just select you were referred to Omdena and enter the code.  Getting selected to take part in Omdena challenge is very competitive, but with the code, you stand a better chance. After several applications and rejections, I got an invite through a member's code. Taking part in the project can boost your profile for better opportunities in the industry, you can include it as part of your work experience. And as you collaborate with other AI engineers and data scientists around the world, you learn more.  If you so wish to take the advantage of joining Omdena collaborators, to develop your skills, get recognised and make an impact, apply for Omdena projects of your choice and use this code HOV7RYSL0QX3FQ.  To know more about Omdena challenge, visit https://omdena.com/projects/#our_challenges  If you have any questions, feel free to ask.  Thanks.

author: Fabiyi Opeyemi
message: *```The Maiden edition of dbt Meetup in Nigeria*```   The Modern Data stack and the rise of Analytics Engineering isn't just some random speculation, instead, it's gradually becoming a highly sought after skill every organization would need to stay relevant in coming years.   Becoming a Data Engineer can be quite tedious with a high learning curve compared to becoming an Analytics Engineer. Fortunately, Data analyst and data scientist are at an advantage as they can easily pick up the AE stack leveraging on their existing Analytics knowledge which would ensure a seemless integration into the Analytics Engineering role.   It's exciting to know that with the advent of an amazing tool like dbt, data analysts and engineers can now build analytics the way engineers build applications.  In the light of this, We are super excited  to announce the start off of dbt meetup here in Nigeria, which is dedicated to helping data analyst and all data professionals own thier analytics engineering workflow _across all industries_   A lot of  interesting conversations related to the data stacks, data operations, data teams, modeling, testing, dashboards, etc. will be happening in the Meetup and it's definitely one you can't afford to miss out on!  Amazing speakers and interesting topics to look forward to include :   üìå Evolution of the Modern Data stack   üìåSetting up a Modern Data stack from Scratch   üìåNavigating the Remote global job market.   Now, register for the maiden edition coming October 14, 2021 in the link below, also share and invite others   https://www.meetup.com/lagos-dbt-meetup/
